715292f-a.title: Manhattan: 123rd Street (West) - St. Nicholas Avenue
715292f-a.text:
West 123rd Street, east from St. Nicholas to Ninth Avenues.
(elevated line at that point). To the right is a 3 story dwelling,
No. 312 West 123rd Street, at the S.E. corner of St. Nicholas Ave.
March 19, 1938.
P. L. Sperr,
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

723121f-a.title: Manhattan: St. Nicholas Avenue - 123rd Street (West)
723121f-a.text:
St. Nicholas Avenue, east side, south from W. 123rd Street
(exxtreme right and not seen ). This thoroumhfare crosses Eighth
venue and upon which apears the Ninth Avenue ''El''. The row
of buildings beyond hame, form the east side of Eighth Avenue,
from 121st Street to 122nd Street. At this point in earlier
days, Bensons Lane branched eastward from the Harlem Road to Ninas-
bridge. The latter followed the preset line of St. Nicholas
Avenue.
March 19, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
